description:
&lt;p&gt;Looking for a role in Acute Medicine? We are looking for staff to work on our Medical Assessment Unit (Ward 8). The MAU team works closely with the A&amp;E department and treats a variety of patients in a fast paced environment. The role will provide you with valuable experience in Acute Medicine and build your knowledge, skills and confidence in this area. Whilst experienced nurses are desired with post registration experience, newly qualified nurses will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of your role you will required to assess patients in order to prioritise an acute and busy workload and put into practice treatment plans in collaboration with the medical team. You will also work closely with the multi-disciplinary team to provide efficient and holistic care to patients. The successful candidate will be confident with their communication skills and will have a desire to learn extended skills such as venepuncture, cannulation and catheterisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a high level of support on the ward for new starters along with a structured induction which will help to develop your skills and teach you the knowledge you will need to succeed. There will also be training available and, once you have gained experience, there will be opportunities to progress further within your career in the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work shifts and flexibility is required. A rotational post within Urgent Care / ICU may be considered for those looking for experience in a variety of areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift patterns: shifts will be either early (07.30-15.30), late (13.30-20.30), long day (07.30-20.30) or night shifts (20.00-08.00).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For details about the role and ward/informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nina Bayley&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;nina.bayley@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01625 663793&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
